{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1280,"text":"Getting a college education"},{"time":3325,"text":"is a 20-year investment."},{"time":6400,"text":"When you're growing up poor,"},{"time":8080,"text":"you're not accustomed\nto thinking that far ahead."},{"time":11040,"text":"Instead, you're thinking about\nwhere you're going to get your next meal"},{"time":14400,"text":"and how your family\nis going to pay rent that month."},{"time":17280,"text":"Besides, my parents\nand my friends' parents"},{"time":20440,"text":"seemed to be doing just fine\ndriving taxis and working as janitors."},{"time":24920,"text":"It wasn't until I was a teenager"},{"time":26840,"text":"when I realized I didn't\nwant to do those things."},{"time":30120,"text":"By then, I was two-thirds of the way\nthrough my education,"},{"time":33760,"text":"and it was almost too late\nto turn things around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37680,"text":"When you grow up poor,\nyou want to be rich."},{"time":40800,"text":"I was no different."},{"time":42600,"text":"I'm the second-oldest of seven,"},{"time":44360,"text":"and was raised by a single mother\non government aid"},{"time":46800,"text":"in Queens, New York."},{"time":48720,"text":"By virtue of growing up low-income,"},{"time":50680,"text":"my siblings and I went\nto some of New York City's"},{"time":53040,"text":"most struggling public schools."},{"time":55200,"text":"I had over 60 absences\nwhen I was in seventh grade,"},{"time":59280,"text":"because I didn't feel like going to class."},{"time":61880,"text":"My high school had\na 55 percent graduation rate,"},{"time":64959,"text":"and even worse,"},{"time":66280,"text":"only 20 percent of the kids graduating"},{"time":68600,"text":"were college-ready."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70960,"text":"When I actually did make it to college,"},{"time":73120,"text":"I told my friend Brennan"},{"time":74560,"text":"how our teachers would always ask us\nto raise our hands"},{"time":78280,"text":"if we were going to college."},{"time":81400,"text":"I was taken aback when Brennan said,"},{"time":83160,"text":"\"Karim, I've never been asked\nthat question before.\""},{"time":86720,"text":"It was always, \"What college\nare you going to?\""},{"time":89720,"text":"Just the way that question is phrased"},{"time":91680,"text":"made it unacceptable for him\nnot to have gone to college."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95960,"text":"Nowadays I get asked a different question."},{"time":98680,"text":"\"How were you able to make it out?\""},{"time":101760,"text":"For years I said I was lucky,"},{"time":105320,"text":"but it's not just luck."},{"time":107280,"text":"When my older brother and I\ngraduated from high school"},{"time":109880,"text":"at the very same time"},{"time":111160,"text":"and he later dropped out\nof a two-year college,"},{"time":113400,"text":"I wanted to understand why he dropped out"},{"time":115880,"text":"and I kept studying."},{"time":118240,"text":"It wasn't until I got to Cornell\nas a Presidential Research Scholar"},{"time":121640,"text":"that I started to learn about\nthe very real educational consequences"},{"time":125400,"text":"of being raised by a single mother\non government aid"},{"time":128199,"text":"and attending the schools that I did."},{"time":130919,"text":"That's when my older brother's trajectory\nbegan to make complete sense to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":136280,"text":"I also learned that our most admirable\neducation reformers,"},{"time":139680,"text":"people like Arne Duncan,\nthe former US Secretary of Education,"},{"time":143360,"text":"or Wendy Kopp, the founder\nof Teach For America,"},{"time":146080,"text":"had never attended an inner city\npublic school like I had."},{"time":149520,"text":"So much of our education reform\nis driven by a sympathetic approach,"},{"time":153360,"text":"where people are saying,"},{"time":154640,"text":"\"Let's go and help\nthese poor inner city kids,"},{"time":157680,"text":"or these poor black and Latino kids,\""},{"time":160320,"text":"instead of an empathetic approach,"},{"time":162720,"text":"where someone like me, who had grown up\nin this environment, could say,"},{"time":166160,"text":"\"I know the adversities that you're facing"},{"time":168400,"text":"and I want to help you overcome them.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":171560,"text":"Today when I get questions\nabout how I made it out,"},{"time":174280,"text":"I share that one of the biggest reasons"},{"time":176800,"text":"is that I wasn't ashamed to ask for help."},{"time":179840,"text":"In a typical middle class\nor affluent household,"},{"time":182480,"text":"if a kid is struggling,"},{"time":184280,"text":"there's a good chance that a parent\nor a teacher will come to their rescue"},{"time":188240,"text":"even if they don't ask for help."},{"time":190200,"text":"However, if that same kid\nis growing up poor"},{"time":192360,"text":"and doesn't ask for help,"},{"time":194240,"text":"there's a good chance\nthat no one will help them."},{"time":196880,"text":"There are virtually\nno social safety nets available."}]},{"cues":[{"time":201160,"text":"So seven years ago,"},{"time":202560,"text":"I started to reform\nour public education system"},{"time":205400,"text":"shaped by my firsthand perspective."},{"time":208960,"text":"And I started with summer school."},{"time":211960,"text":"Research tells us that two-thirds\nof the achievement gap,"},{"time":215320,"text":"which is the disparity\nin educational attainment"},{"time":217680,"text":"between rich kids and poor kids"},{"time":219880,"text":"or black kids and white kids,"},{"time":222040,"text":"could be directly attributed\nto the summer learning loss."},{"time":225640,"text":"In low-income neighborhoods,\nkids forget almost three months"},{"time":228480,"text":"of what they learned\nduring the school year"},{"time":230560,"text":"over the summer."},{"time":231920,"text":"They return to school in the fall,"},{"time":233560,"text":"and their teachers\nspend another two months"},{"time":235640,"text":"reteaching them old material."},{"time":237080,"text":"That's five months."},{"time":238600,"text":"The school year in the United States\nis only 10 months."},{"time":241240,"text":"If kids lose five months of learning\nevery single year,"},{"time":243880,"text":"that's half of their education."},{"time":246120,"text":"Half."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248080,"text":"If kids were in school over the summer,\nthen they couldn't regress,"},{"time":252000,"text":"but traditional summer school\nis poorly designed."},{"time":254920,"text":"For kids it feels like punishment,"},{"time":257000,"text":"and for teachers\nit feels like babysitting."},{"time":260320,"text":"But how can we expect principals\nto execute an effective summer program"},{"time":264360,"text":"when the school year\nends the last week of June"},{"time":266840,"text":"and then summer school starts\njust one week later?"},{"time":269960,"text":"There just isn't enough time\nto find the right people,"},{"time":272560,"text":"sort out the logistics,"},{"time":273840,"text":"and design an engaging curriculum\nthat excites kids and teachers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279760,"text":"But what if we created a program\nover the summer"},{"time":283760,"text":"that empowered teachers\nas teaching coaches"},{"time":287480,"text":"to develop aspiring educators?"},{"time":290720,"text":"What if we empowered\ncollege-educated role models"},{"time":293480,"text":"as teaching fellows"},{"time":295560,"text":"to help kids realize\ntheir college ambitions?"},{"time":298120,"text":"What if empowered high-achieving kids"},{"time":300400,"text":"as mentors to tutor their younger peers"},{"time":303840,"text":"and inspire them\nto invest in their education?"},{"time":307640,"text":"What if we empowered all kids as scholars,"},{"time":311400,"text":"asked them what colleges\nthey were going to,"},{"time":314640,"text":"designed a summer school\nthey want to attend"},{"time":318400,"text":"to completely eliminate\nthe summer learning loss"},{"time":320960,"text":"and close two-thirds\nof the achievement gap?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":325280,"text":"By this summer, my team will have served\nover 4,000 low-income children,"},{"time":329920,"text":"trained over 300 aspiring teachers"},{"time":332880,"text":"and created more than 1,000 seasonal jobs"},{"time":335200,"text":"across some of New York City's\nmost disadvantaged neighborhoods."}]},{"cues":[{"time":339000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":344840,"text":"And our kids are succeeding."},{"time":347200,"text":"Two years of independent evaluations"},{"time":349200,"text":"tell us that our kids\neliminate the summer learning loss"},{"time":352160,"text":"and make growth of one month in math"},{"time":354360,"text":"and two months in reading."},{"time":356200,"text":"So instead of returning to school\nin the fall three months behind,"},{"time":359720,"text":"they now go back four months ahead in math"},{"time":363560,"text":"and five months ahead in reading."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365640,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":372760,"text":"Ten years ago, if you would have told me"},{"time":374720,"text":"that I'd graduate in the top 10 percent\nof my class from an Ivy League institution"},{"time":378920,"text":"and have an opportunity to make a dent\non our public education system"},{"time":382920,"text":"just by tackling two months\nof the calendar year,"},{"time":386680,"text":"I would have said,"},{"time":388440,"text":"\"Nah. No way.\""},{"time":391720,"text":"What's even more exciting"},{"time":393240,"text":"is that if we can prevent\nfive months of lost time"},{"time":396440,"text":"just by redesigning two months,"},{"time":399480,"text":"imagine the possibilities\nthat we can unlock"},{"time":402160,"text":"by tackling the rest of the calendar year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406160,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":407400,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}